<h1>Access Permissions</h1>

<p>This application defines three main roles: <strong>Regular Employee</strong>, <strong>HR</strong>, and <strong>Admin</strong>. Each role has specific access permissions as described below:</p>

<hr />

<h2>Regular Employee Permissions</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Can view <strong>Departments</strong> and <strong>Employees</strong> data.</li>
    <li>
        Has read-only access:
        <ul>
            <li>Can view details of employees and departments.</li>
            <li>Cannot create, edit, or delete any data.</li>
            <li>Cannot access user accounts or roles management.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h2>HR Permissions</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Can access the <strong>Departments</strong> section.</li>
    <li>Can access the <strong>Employees</strong> section.</li>
    <li>
        Can perform the following actions on both:
        <ul>
            <li>Create</li>
            <li>Edit</li>
            <li>Delete</li>
            <li>View Details</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<h2>Admin Permissions</h2>
<ul>
    <li>Has all the permissions of the HR role.</li>
    <li>
        Additionally, can access and manage:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>User Accounts</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Roles</strong></li>
        </ul>
    </li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h3>Note</h3>
<p>Unauthorized access to restricted pages will redirect the user to the access denied page or login screen.</p>
